<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I create a DB object at bootstrap by $db = Zend_Db::factory($database_config), and store it into the Registry for later use.</p>

<p>$database_config is a Zend_Config object containing the adapter, params etc...</p>

<p>The problem here, is when I use a mixture of databases, say MSSQL &amp; MYSQL.
The SQL statements for the two databases potentially differ.</p>

<p>So when writing DAOs, I need to cater for the differences. I need to know what adapter (or database type) that the $db object represents.</p>

<p>getDbConfig() returns params, but no adapter type.</p>

<p>I note that there is a _pdoType in some DB Adapters, but its protected. However, this will only apply to PDO I guess.</p>

<p>Can I request that getDbConfig() be extended to include adapter information?
or a new function getDbAdapter().</p>

